author: AccessWDUN staff
title: Jefferson blanks East Jackson
text:
Saturday October 17th, 2015 3:27AM Posted 8:45AM on Saturday 17th October 2015 ( 5 hours from now ) Jefferson blanks East Jackson By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 8: Surprises abound in wild night of prep football VIDEO: Rabun County routs Union County in top 10 showdown, 49-3 
COMMERCE — Class AAA No. 3 Jefferson remained unbeaten after taking a 49-0 win over East Jackson Friday in Region 8-AAA action. 
The Dragons (8-0, 4-0 Region 8-AAA) started fast with 35 first quarter points en route to the big win. 
Sophomore running back Colby Wood played just seven offensive plays for the Dragons but was more than effective carrying the five times for 113 yards and a touchdown. Zach Boobas had two rushing touchdowns and added a pick-6 on defense. 
Darian Hill had two touchdowns and quarterback Zach Corbin had one score for Jefferson, which piled up 321 total yards of offense. 
The Dragons defense held East Jackson (1-7, 0-4) to just 61 total yards of offense. 
Jefferson will have a bye week next Friday before taking on Oconee County in Watkinsville in two weeks in what is expected to be a battle for first place in the region.
